to move file

mv 
mv source destination
mv -i source destination

eg. mv dir firstdir

Sorting data

sort file 
sort text in file

eg: using this with sort
-k F // by the second field
-R reverse order
-u unique order // remove duplicate


Creating a collection of files

tar [-] c|x|t f tarfile [path]

some of the commonly used tar options

c create a tar archive
x extract files from the archive
t displat the table of contents
v be verbose
z use compression
f file use this file

eg. 
tar cf tps.tar tpsreports
tar tf tps.tar
tar xf tps.tar

compress file

gzip
gunzip
gzcat concatenates compressed files
zcat 

